<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="68" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,304,461,487]" box="[189,304,461,487]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,304,461,487]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,461,487]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[188,1399,508,710]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
<bibRefCitation author="Grouvelle M. A." box="[189,394,508,534]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="365 - 380" refId="ref6132" refString="Grouvelle M. A. 1908. Collections recueillies par M. Maurice de Rothschild dans l'Afrique orientale anglaise. Insectes Coleopteres: Clavicornes. Diagnoses des especes nouvelles. Bulletin du Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris 14 (7): 365 - 380." type="journal article" year="1908">Grouvelle (1908)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1908" box="[526,736,508,534]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Atritomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis box="[526,736,508,534]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Atritomus vicinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single male collected by Rothschild in 
<collectingCountry box="[1299,1398,508,534]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild M. &amp; M. le Baron Maurice de Rothschild" box="[199,408,543,569]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref7065" refString="Rothschild M. (ed.) 1922 a. Voyage de M. le Baron Maurice de Rothschild en Ethiopie et en Afrique orientale anglaise (1904 - 1905). Resultats scientifiques. Animaux articules. Deuxieme partie. Imprimerie Nationale, Paris." type="book" year="1922">Rothschild 1922a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild M. &amp; M. le Baron Maurice de Rothschild" box="[419,498,543,570]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref7111" refString="Rothschild M. (ed.) 1922 b. Voyage de M. le Baron Maurice de Rothschild en Ethiopie et en Afrique orientale anglaise (1904 - 1905). Resultats scientifiques. Animaux articules. Atlas. Imprimerie Nationale, Paris." type="book" year="1922">1922b</bibRefCitation>
). This species, listed under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1877" box="[813,930,543,569]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Atritomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,930,543,569]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Atritomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hetschko A." box="[1027,1225,543,569]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref6246" refString="Hetschko A. 1930. Fam. Mycetophagidae. In: Junk W. &amp; Schenkling S. (eds) Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 108: 1 - 26. W. Junk, Berlin." type="journal article" year="1930">Hetschko (1930)</bibRefCitation>
, was no longer mentioned by any of the subsequent authors. Although we have not yet been able to directly access the 
<typeStatus box="[189,292,613,639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1908" box="[332,449,614,640]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Atritomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis box="[332,449,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">A. vicinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for dissection, because of restrictions due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the highresolution images provided by our colleague Antoine Mantilleri (MNHN) (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1152,649,675]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[308,1270,294,1860]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[261,1327,265,1889]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 2. Atritomus vicinus Grouvelle, 1908 (= Typhaeola vicina (Grouvelle, 1908) comb. nov.), holotype (EC12477). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. C. Habitus, ventral view. D. Labels. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6811528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6811528/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) allowed us to place this species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Ganglbauer, 1899" authorityName="Ganglbauer" authorityYear="1899" box="[480,822,684,710]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Typhaeola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[480,603,684,710]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Typhaeola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ganglbauer L." box="[610,822,684,710]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref6074" refString="Ganglbauer L. 1899. Die Kafer von Mitteleuropa. 3. Familienreihe Clavicornia. Carl Gerold's Sohn, Wien." type="book" year="1899">Ganglbauer, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
